    <div align='center'>
        <font size='4'><b>LASLO BALINT PLANNING LARGE SCALE CHARITY EFFORT</b></font><br>
                                <img src='http://graphics.millsberry.com/site_gfx/interiors/gazette/gazette_20081016.jpg' border='1' width='280' height='200'>
                        </div>
        <div id='gazette_byline'><em>By Everett F. Stevens<br>Editor-in-Chief</em></div>
        <b>Thursday, October 16, 2008</b> &mdash;
    In a press conference held today, it was announced that Laslo Balint is beginning a large scale cause related undertaking.<br><br>A recent inheritance from a great uncle has allowed Laslo to put forward a sizeable contribution to the effort.<br><br>&quot;It was recently discovered that my great uncle, Dexter Balint, had left the majority of his Ravenwood estate to me,&quot; commented Balint.<br><br>&quot;At first, I wasn&#039;t quite sure what to do with this inheritance, but then the wheels started turning.&quot;<br><br>&quot;The plans and details are still being hashed out, but when the project is finished, I hope to leave a forum for everyone to come together in Millsberry for the greater good of those here and abroad.&quot;<br>
<br>
Laslo Balint is hoping to inspire others to take up similar projects. He believes that anyone determined enough can make a difference. <br><br>&quot;Change always starts with one person. With the right attitude and perseverance, anyone can accomplish anything.&quot;<br><br>To help everyone else get in the spirit, Laslo has provided <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">special commemorative bricks</a> that will be sold to help raise additional funds for the upcoming cause related effort.<br><br>Along with this is the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Ground Breaking Shovel</a>, the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Ribbon Cutting Ceremony Kit</a>, and a <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/shop.phtml?shop_id=7">Grand Opening Kit</a>. <br><br>It&#039;s everything you&#039;ll need to take on your own cause related efforts. <br><br>&quot;I&#039;m hoping to create a new mobile center to house future cause related efforts in Millsberry. We&#039;re not quite sure what or where this center will be yet.&quot; <br><br>&quot;The plans are still being drawn up, but rest assured, it&#039;s going to be an exciting unveiling.&quot;<br><br>&quot;It&#039;s always great to see your plans and dreams come together and actually be realized, so I can&#039;t tell you how happy I am about this upcoming charitable event.&quot;<br><br>&quot;Stay tuned. I hope that many of you will be involved.&quot;<br><br>Now that Laslo has us all on the edge of our seats, we&#039;re all waiting eagerly to see what he has in store. 
    </div>

        

<br><hr><br>

<div id='gazette_story'>
    <div align='center'>
        <font size='3'><b>MEET THE CANDIDATES</b></font><br>
                                <BR>
                        </div>
        <b>Thursday, October 16, 2008</b> &mdash;
    The candidates for the upcoming Mayoral Election were announced yesterday. In the running are Hunter Lopez, Douglas Wright, and Allison McCarthy. Each candidate gave a speech in front of an excited Millsberry audience. Lopez has been a Millsberry citizen for 11 years now and has been involved in many civic efforts, most notably last spring&#039;s Feed Children of Malawi. He plans to focus Millsberry more on cause related efforts both in the city and abroad. Douglas Wright has been a citizen for 8 years, and is planning a campaign centered on city-wide improvements. Allison McCarthy is planning to run a campaign focused primarily on environmentally friendly living. 
    </div>

